# Limit clang-format enforcement for now. Each block below ignores one folder's
# whole subtree. To start enforcing a folder, delete its block.
#
# NOTE: clang-format 19 does NOT implement the "**" globstar (it collapses "**"
# into a single "*"), and a single "*" matches exactly ONE path segment. A
# trailing "*" only matches files that have no further sub-directories. So
# "score/json/*" ignores ONLY direct children of score/json, not nested files.
# Because no single pattern matches an arbitrary depth, each folder is expanded
# to one line per nesting level (sized to its current deepest file). If a folder
# later gains deeper files, add another "/*" line.
# See https://clang.llvm.org/docs/ClangFormat.html#clang-format-ignore

